const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What is the best job management software for solar installers in Australia?",
    answer: "ServiceM8 is widely regarded as the best job management software for Australian solar installers in 2026. It is specifically built for compliance-heavy trades, supporting CER checklists, STC documentation, AS/NZS 5033 and 5139 sign-off forms, and digital evidence capture. For smaller operations with simpler compliance needs, Tradify and Fergus are cost-effective alternatives."
  },
  {
    question: "Does ServiceM8 work for CER compliance documentation?",
    answer: "Yes. ServiceM8 supports CER (Clean Energy Regulator) compliance documentation through customisable job templates and checklists. Installers can build CER-specific inspection forms, attach timestamped photos, and capture digital client sign-offs — all stored against the job record for audit purposes. This makes it well-suited to CER-accredited businesses subject to compliance audits."
  },
  {
    question: "How do solar installers manage STC paperwork digitally?",
    answer: "Solar installers can manage STC (Small-scale Technology Certificate) paperwork digitally using job management platforms like ServiceM8. The typical workflow involves attaching system design documents and installation evidence to the job record, capturing photos of the completed installation, obtaining digital client sign-off, and exporting job records for submission to the STC registry. ServiceM8's templating system allows STC-specific forms to be built once and reused across all jobs."
  },
  {
    question: "What software do Australian electricians use for job management?",
